Component,Platform,Why it's best for you
Database,Supabase or Aiven,Supabase offers a professional PostgreSQL DB that handles 50k rows easily. Aiven offers a free 5GB plan which is huge.
Backend,Render or Koyeb,"Both allow you to deploy Spring Boot for free. Koyeb is faster for Java, while Render is very beginner-friendly."
Frontend,Netlify or Vercel,"They provide a Permanent HTTPS Link (e.g., attendance-system.netlify.app) for free."
attendance-management-system/
│
├── backend/ (Spring Boot)
│   ├── src/main/java/com/attendance/
│   │   ├── AttendanceApplication.java      # Main entry point
│   │   │
│   │   ├── config/
│   │   │   ├── SecurityConfig.java         # Roles and JWT setup
│   │   │   └── JwtFilter.java              # Token validation logic
│   │   │
│   │   ├── controller/
│   │   │   ├── AuthController.java         # Login/Signup
│   │   │   ├── AdminController.java        # Manage 50k users, rooms
│   │   │   ├── TeacherController.java      # Generate 5-min PIN
│   │   │   └── StudentController.java      # Submit PIN and IP
│   │   │
│   │   ├── service/
│   │   │   ├── AuthService.java            # Password hashing
│   │   │   ├── AttendanceService.java      # PIN/WiFi/Time validation
│   │   │   └── AdminService.java           # Data analysis & Reports
│   │   │
│   │   ├── repository/
│   │   │   ├── UserRepository.java         # JPA queries
│   │   │   ├── SessionRepository.java      # OTP lookup
│   │   │   └── AttendanceRepository.java   # Record keeping
│   │   │
│   │   ├── model/ (Entities)
│   │   │   ├── User.java                   # Admin/Teacher/Student
│   │   │   ├── Classroom.java              # Holds WiFi IP data
│   │   │   ├── AttendanceSession.java      # Holds 5-min OTP logic
│   │   │   └── AttendanceRecord.java       # Final status logs
│   │   │
│   │   ├── dto/ (Data Transfer Objects)
│   │   │   ├── AuthRequest.java            # Login payload
│   │   │   ├── AttendanceSubmit.java       # Student submission payload
│   │   │   └── UserResponse.java           # For cleaning data output
│   │   │
│   │   └── exception/
│   │       └── GlobalExceptionHandler.java # Error handling for 50k records
│   │
│   └── src/main/resources/
│       ├── application.properties          # Database & Port config
│       └── data.sql                        # Default setup (Postgres)
│
├── frontend/ (Static Web Files)
│   ├── index.html                          # Main Login
│   ├── dashboard-admin.html                # User/Class management
│   ├── dashboard-teacher.html              # PIN display & Permissions
│   ├── dashboard-student.html              # PIN entry
│   │
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── global.css                      # Simple styling
│   │
│   └── js/
│       ├── api.js                          # Shared Fetch() config
│       ├── admin.js                        # Admin logic
│       ├── teacher.js                      # Timer/PIN logic
│       └── student.js                      # IP/Geolocation logic
│
└── database/
    └── schema_design.sql                   # SQL for Table indexing
